{"type": "root", "attrs": {}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Houdini user interface"], "extent": [0, 27]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [27, 43], "body": [{"type": "vimeo_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "vimeo", "indent": 0, "text": [" Houdini workspace"], "role": "item", "extent": [43, 70], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "113734396"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/ui/main_window.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [90, 126]}, {"type": "col_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [126, 132], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["1. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/menus", "type": "link", "text": ["Main menus"], "fullpath": "/ref/menus"}], "extent": [132, 164], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The main menus at the top are always the same, and provide quick access to common functionality, such as importing files and managing renders."], "extent": [164, 316]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/", "type": "link", "text": ["Shelf"], "fullpath": "/shelf/index"}], "extent": [316, 340], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The shelf contains a large array of useful tools for working interactively in the scene view. You can ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/windows/edittool", "type": "link", "text": ["create your own custom scripted tools"], "fullpath": "/ref/windows/edittool"}, " here for quick access."], "extent": [340, 536]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["3. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "view", "type": "link", "text": ["3D scene view"], "fullpath": "/basics/view"}], "extent": [536, 565], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The Scene View pane shows a 3D representation of the current scene file. You can change the shading style and increase or decrease the display quality. The controls in the pane header let you change the viewport layout and shading style."], "extent": [565, 812]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["4. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#toolbox", "type": "link", "text": ["Toolbox"], "fullpath": "/basics/ui#toolbox", "fragment": "#toolbox"}], "extent": [812, 839], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The toolbox is a collection of very commonly used tools, such as select, move, rotate, and scale, as well as toggles such as ", {"scheme": null, "value": "inspection", "type": "link", "text": ["inspection mode"], "fullpath": "/basics/inspection"}, " and ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/model/aids", "type": "link", "text": ["snapping"], "fullpath": "/model/aids"}, "."], "extent": [839, 1030]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["5. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#opbar", "type": "link", "text": ["Operation toolbar"], "fullpath": "/basics/ui#opbar", "fragment": "#opbar"}], "extent": [1030, 1065], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The toolbar at the top of the scene view shows important controls for the currently selected node. You can use these controls if you work in the view with the parameter editor minimized."], "extent": [1065, 1261]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["6. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "view", "type": "link", "text": ["Display options"], "fullpath": "/basics/view"}], "extent": [1261, 1292], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The icon buttons on the right side of the view give you quick access to commonly used display options. You can click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "BUTTONS/displayoptions", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/BUTTONS/displayoptions"}, " display options button on this toolbar to open the full display options window."], "extent": [1292, 1532]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1532, 1538], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["7. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/network/parms", "type": "link", "text": ["Parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/network/parms"}], "extent": [1538, 1580], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This pane lets you edit the parameters of the currently selected node to change how it works."], "extent": [1580, 1683]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["8. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/network/nodes", "type": "link", "text": ["Network editor"], "fullpath": "/network/nodes"}], "extent": [1683, 1723], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This pane shows the nodes in the current network. You can create nodes, select them to see their parameters in the parameter editor, and ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/network/wire", "type": "link", "text": ["wire them together"], "fullpath": "/network/wire"}, "."], "extent": [1723, 1905]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["9. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/anim/playbar", "type": "link", "text": ["Playbar"], "fullpath": "/anim/playbar"}], "extent": [1905, 1937], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The playbar has playback controls and the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["timeline"]}, ", which lets you scrub across the animation frames, and shows which frames have ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/anim/basics", "type": "link", "text": ["keys"], "fullpath": "/anim/basics"}, "."], "extent": [1937, 2099]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["10. Help button and take controls"], "extent": [2099, 2138], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Click the Help button to open the online help browser in a side pane. This is very useful for viewing the help while continuing to work in Houdini. See the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "takes", "type": "link", "text": ["takes page"], "fullpath": "/basics/takes"}, " for information about the take controls."], "extent": [2138, 2363]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["11. Status line"], "extent": [2363, 2384], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The line at the bottom of the main window displays status and progress updates as you work."], "extent": [2384, 2489]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["12. ", {"scheme": null, "value": "cooking", "type": "link", "text": ["Cook controls"], "fullpath": "/basics/cooking"}], "extent": [2489, 2522], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["These controls let you turn off automatic refresh of the scene view if your scene is extremely complex and slow to update. See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "cooking", "type": "link", "text": ["cooking"], "fullpath": "/basics/cooking"}, " for more information."], "extent": [2522, 2698]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Working in Houdini"], "extent": [2698, 2723], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Houdini has two main complementary ways of interaction:"], "extent": [2723, 2781]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/", "type": "link", "text": ["shelf tools"], "fullpath": "/shelf/index"}, " in the scene view. The scripted tools create nodes for you in the background."], "extent": [2781, 2894]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creating nodes directly in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/panes/network", "type": "link", "text": ["network editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/network"}, " using the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "tabmenu", "type": "link", "text": ["tab menu"], "fullpath": "/basics/tabmenu"}, "."], "extent": [2894, 2994]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["New users will probably be most comfortable just using the shelf tools at first, and some users (for example, character animators) will never need to create their own nodes. However, for modeling and effects work, getting the most out of Houdini usually involves shifting back and forth between the two styles. You will often use the shelf tools as easy ways to start or change a network, and also add and edit nodes to make more complex networks."], "extent": [2994, 3443]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "toolbox", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Toolbox"], "extent": [3443, 3467], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The toolbox is located on the left side of the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/views/3dview", "type": "link", "text": ["scene view"], "fullpath": "/ref/views/3dview"}, ". It provides selection, transforming, viewing, and rendering tools, as well as snapping options and menus for starting renders."], "extent": [3467, 3675]}, {"type": "table", "thead": [], "body": [{"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/select_objects", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/select_objects"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/select_faces", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/select_faces"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/select_dynamics", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/select_dynamics"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/select", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/select"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [3675, 3780], "container": true, "attrs": {"width": "32px"}}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/select", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/select"}, " ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["selection tools"]}, " let you select objects or components in the scene view. See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/basics/select", "type": "link", "text": ["selecting objects and components"], "fullpath": "/basics/select"}, "."], "extent": [3797, 3955]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/move", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/move"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/rotate", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/rotate"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/scale", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/scale"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [3955, 4014], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The move, rotate, scale tools let you transform the selection using ", {"scheme": null, "value": "handles", "type": "link", "text": ["handles"], "fullpath": "/basics/handles"}, " in the view."], "extent": [4014, 4118]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/pose", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/pose"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4118, 4138], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/pose", "type": "link", "text": ["Pose tool"], "fullpath": "/shelf/pose"}, " transforms the selection with special options for manipulating character rigs."], "extent": [4138, 4250]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/handles", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/handles"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4250, 4273], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "handles", "type": "link", "text": ["Handles tool"], "fullpath": "/basics/handles"}, " shows the node-specific handles for the current node. You can also press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to switch to the Handles tool in the viewer."], "extent": [4273, 4433]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/snap_grid", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/snap_grid"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/snap_curve", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/snap_curve"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/snap_point", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/snap_point"}, "\n", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/snap", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/snap"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4433, 4524], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The snapping toggles let you turn snapping to grid, curves, points, and multi-snapping on or off. See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/model/aids", "type": "link", "text": ["snapping"], "fullpath": "/model/aids"}, " for more information."], "extent": [4524, 4676]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/view", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/view"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4676, 4696], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The view tool lets you ", {"scheme": null, "value": "view", "type": "link", "text": ["track, tumble, and dolly"], "fullpath": "/basics/view"}, " the view. Instead of selecting this tool directly, you will usually hold ", {"keys": ["Space"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to enter it temporarily while you work."], "extent": [4696, 4879]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/render_region", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/render_region"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [4879, 4908], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/render/renderregion", "type": "link", "text": ["render region tool"], "fullpath": "/render/renderregion"}, " lets you draw a box around part of the view and see it rendered. The rendering updates automatically as you work."], "extent": [4908, 5073]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/inspect", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/inspect"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [5073, 5096], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can turn on the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "inspection", "type": "link", "text": ["inspection mode"], "fullpath": "/basics/inspection"}, " to show a floating window near the mouse pointer with extra information about what\u2019s under the pointer. This is especially useful in image views such as the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/render/render", "type": "link", "text": ["render view"], "fullpath": "/render/render"}, "."], "extent": [5096, 5337]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/flipbook", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/TOOLS/flipbook"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [5337, 5361], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The  Flipbook button lets you capture playback in the viewer as an animation. See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/render/flipbook", "type": "link", "text": ["flipbooking"], "fullpath": "/render/flipbook"}, " for more information."], "extent": [5361, 5501]}]}], "divider": false}, {"type": "row", "body": [{"type": "cell", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Icon", "value": "NETWORKS/rop", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/NETWORKS/rop"}, " "], "role": "td", "extent": [5501, 5523], "container": true}, {"type": "cell", "role": "td", "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The  Render menu button provides a quick way to ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/render/render", "type": "link", "text": ["render to a window"], "fullpath": "/render/render"}, ". This button is less useful than in older versions of Houdini, since now you can use the Render View tab to preview renders, and the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Render"]}, " menu (in the main menus) to set up and launch final renders."], "extent": [5523, 5817]}]}], "divider": false}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "opbar", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Operation control toolbar"], "extent": [5817, 5857], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When you use a tool on the shelf, or select a node in the network editor, the node\u2019s most important parameters appear on a toolbar above the 3D scene view. These controls let you modify the tool/node\u2019s operation even if the parameter editor is not visible. You can also click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "BUTTONS/help", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/basics/BUTTONS/help"}, " Help button at the end of the toolbar to see the help for the current operation."], "extent": [5857, 6241]}]}], "title": ["Houdini user interface"]}